            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-32141",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "flatted: flatted: Unbounded recursion DoS in parse() revive phase"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "flatted is a circular JSON parser. Prior to 3.4.0, flatted's parse() function uses a recursive revive() phase to resolve circular references in deserialized JSON. When given a crafted payload with deeply nested or self-referential $ indices, the recursion depth is unbounded, causing a stack overflow that crashes the Node.js process. This vulnerability is fixed in 3.4.0."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-32141",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-32141\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: flatted\nFixed Version: 3.4.0\nLink: [CVE-2026-32141](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-32141)\nflatted is a circular JSON parser. Prior to 3.4.0, flatted's parse() function uses a recursive revive() phase to resolve circular references in deserialized JSON. When given a crafted payload with deeply nested or self-referential $ indices, the recursion depth is unbounded, causing a stack overflow that crashes the Node.js process. This vulnerability is fixed in 3.4.0.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-32141**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|flatted|3.4.0|[CVE-2026-32141](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-32141)|\n\nflatted is a circular JSON parser. Prior to 3.4.0, flatted's parse() function uses a recursive revive() phase to resolve circular references in deserialized JSON. When given a crafted payload with deeply nested or self-referential $ indices, the recursion depth is unbounded, causing a stack overflow that crashes the Node.js process. This vulnerability is fixed in 3.4.0."
              },
