                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-29786",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "node-tar: hardlink path traversal via drive-relative linkpath"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "node-tar is a full-featured Tar for Node.js. Prior to version 7.5.10, tar can be tricked into creating a hardlink that points outside the extraction directory by using a drive-relative link target such as C:../target.txt, which enables file overwrite outside cwd during normal tar.x() extraction. This issue has been patched in version 7.5.10."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-29786",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-29786\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: tar\nFixed Version: 7.5.10\nLink: [CVE-2026-29786](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-29786)\nnode-tar is a full-featured Tar for Node.js. Prior to version 7.5.10, tar can be tricked into creating a hardlink that points outside the extraction directory by using a drive-relative link target such as C:../target.txt, which enables file overwrite outside cwd during normal tar.x() extraction. This issue has been patched in version 7.5.10.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-29786**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|tar|7.5.10|[CVE-2026-29786](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-29786)|\n\nnode-tar is a full-featured Tar for Node.js. Prior to version 7.5.10, tar can be tricked into creating a hardlink that points outside the extraction directory by using a drive-relative link target such as C:../target.txt, which enables file overwrite outside cwd during normal tar.x() extraction. This issue has been patched in version 7.5.10."
              },
              "properties": {
